Poseidon USB Stack @POSEIDON_PKG_VERSION@
=========================================

A backport of the AROS Poseidon USB stack to AmigaOS 3.2, with the Trident
preferences editor and the full set of USB device classes.


BUILD VARIANT
-------------

  @DEBUG_BACKEND@
  @DEBUG_BACKEND_DESCRIPTION@

The 'off' archive is the normal download. The 'serial' archive is identical
except the stack, classes and tools also emit debug output, for
troubleshooting.


INSTALLATION
------------

  Double-click the Install icon, or run `Installer Install` from a Shell,
  and follow the prompts. A reboot is recommended afterwards so the freshly
  installed poseidon.library and USB classes are picked up.
